---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Rates - Talia Sable" description="Rates and availability">
  <article class="rates">
    <h1>Rates</h1>

    <div class="rates-with-image">
      <div class="rates-content">
        <section class="rates-standard">
      <div class="rate-tier">
        <h2>One Hour: $3,000</h2>
        <p>A concentrated dose of connection. Perfect for when time is precious.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rate-tier">
        <h2>Two Hours: $3,800</h2>
        <p>Time to relax into each other.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rate-tier">
        <h2>Three Hours: $4,400</h2>
        <p>Drinks or a quick bite, then the main event. Enough to actually connect, not just rush through.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rate-tier">
        <h2>Four Hours: $5,000</h2>
        <p>A proper dinner and time together after. The kind of evening where we're the last ones to leave the restaurant.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rate-tier">
        <h2>Six Hours: $6,500</h2>
        <p>Dinner and a gallery. Or a show, drinks, and wherever the night takes us. Space to breathe.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rate-tier incall">
        <p class="note">Incall available: +$400</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="rates-extended">
      <h2>Extended Retreats</h2>

      <div class="rate-tier">
        <h3>Overnight (16 hours): $12,000</h3>
        <p>An evening that doesn't end. Dinner, conversation, connection, and waking up together. Breakfast in bed optional but encouraged.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rate-tier">
        <h3>A Turn of the Earth (24 hours): $17,000</h3>
        <p>A full day and night. We can be tourists in your city, escape to somewhere nearby, or stay in and pretend the outside world doesn't exist. A complete rotation, just us.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rate-tier">
        <h3>Complete Weekend (60 hours): $32,000</h3>
        <p>Friday evening to Monday morning. A mini-vacation, a chance to actually relax together. The kind of time where inside jokes develop and comfort settles in.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rate-tier">
        <h3>Vacation (5 days): $55,000</h3>
        <p>An actual getaway. Hot springs in Iceland, beaches in Bali, or exploring a city neither of us has seen. Adventure, rest, and the delicious intimacy that comes from extended time together.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
      </div>

      <div class="rates-image">
        <img src="/body-lookback.jpg" alt="Talia Sable" />
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="rates-notes">
          <h2>Notes</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>If we haven't met before, a paid video call is required before an extended retreat</li>
            <li>FMTY dates are an overnight minimum</li>
            <li>In-date extensions are $1,500/hour</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
  </article>

  <section class="photo-gallery">
    <div class="gallery-grid">
      <img src="/body-purpleunderwear.jpg" alt="Talia Sable" />
      <img src="/body-lookupwards.jpg" alt="Talia Sable" />
      <img src="/body-bluebathroom.jpg" alt="Talia Sable" />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    width: 100%;
    height: 60vh;
    min-height: 400px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center;
    display: block;
  }

  .rates {
    max-width: 990px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem 4rem;
  }

  .rates h1 {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .rates-with-image {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 450px;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .rates-image {
    position: sticky;
    top: calc(var(--nav-height) + 2rem);
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .rates-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .rates-standard,
  .rates-extended {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .rates-extended h2 {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .rate-tier {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.3);
  }

  .rate-tier:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .rate-tier h2,
  .rate-tier h3 {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .rate-tier h3 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .rate-tier p {
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .incall {
    border-bottom: none;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .note {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .rates-notes {
    background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .rates-notes h2 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .rates-notes ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .rates-notes li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .rates-notes li::before {
    content: "â€¢";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .photo-gallery {
    width: 100%;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .gallery-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
  }

  .gallery-grid img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 500px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center;
    display: block;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .gallery-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .gallery-grid img {
      height: 400px;
    }
    .rates {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .rates-with-image {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .rates-image {
      position: static;
    }

    .rate-tier h2,
    .rate-tier h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }

    .rates-notes {
      padding: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
